column10:
TLDR;
Game sucks ass even if you can get it to run stable. Story is cool tho. Too bad bethesda snubbed obsidian on the timeline for this game. couldve been so much better.

Game was halted because cazador poison wouldnt stop after using antivenom which cause me to not be able to encounter those enemies without reverting to previous saves. Its such a shame. This game has great stories and subplots and the main themes throughout wouldve only been made better if the developers were allowed to refine the gameplay (mostly fighting mechanics). If you know bethesda lore most people are of the opinion that a project lead realized obsidian was going to make a better game than fallout 3 (not hard to do) so they tried to prevent that. I regret to inform everyone that they succeeded. Office politics put a blemish on an otherwise pristine series. and then they went on to really kick the shitty games into overdrive with later installments. Sometimes the old should stand out of the way of the young, Fallout New Vegas was one of those time (lookin at you todd)
